{"data":[{"type":"questionAttempts","id":"17489299","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questionAttempts/17489299"},"attributes":{"position":0,"marks":1,"score":0,"answeredAt":"2025-09-29T04:11:59+09:30","options":[1],"response":null,"finalizedAt":"2025-09-29T04:11:59+09:30"},"relationships":{"user":{"data":{"type":"users","id":"50098"}},"questionSession":{"data":null},"session":{"data":null},"question":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"628"}},"bookmark":{"data":null}}}],"included":[{"type":"questions","id":"628","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questions/628"},"attributes":{"optionProportions":[0.46,0.01,0.41,0.08,0.04]},"relationships":{"item":{"data":{"type":"items","id":"628"}},"activeRevision":{"data":{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"28805"}}}},{"type":"items","id":"628","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/items/628"},"attributes":{"contentType":"question"},"relationships":{"content":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"628"}},"activeRevision":{"data":{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"15002"}},"tags":{"data":[{"type":"tags","id":"2"},{"type":"tags","id":"11"},{"type":"tags","id":"13"},{"type":"tags","id":"24"},{"type":"tags","id":"31"},{"type":"tags","id":"66"},{"type":"tags","id":"72"},{"type":"tags","id":"78"},{"type":"tags","id":"160"},{"type":"tags","id":"1036"},{"type":"tags","id":"1114"},{"type":"tags","id":"1265"},{"type":"tags","id":"1674"},{"type":"tags","id":"2074"},{"type":"tags","id":"2078"},{"type":"tags","id":"4961"},{"type":"tags","id":"4982"},{"type":"tags","id":"4987"},{"type":"tags","id":"4992"},{"type":"tags","id":"11625"},{"type":"tags","id":"11630"},{"type":"tags","id":"11642"},{"type":"tags","id":"11650"}]},"contributions":{"data":[{"type":"contributions","id":"1861"},{"type":"contributions","id":"2508"},{"type":"contributions","id":"2555"},{"type":"contributions","id":"13493"},{"type":"contributions","id":"17028"},{"type":"contributions","id":"42116"},{"type":"contributions","id":"43025"},{"type":"contributions","id":"44258"},{"type":"contributions","id":"44757"}]}},"meta":{"canRevise":false,"canManage":false,"canDelete":false}},{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"28805","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questionRevisions/28805"},"attributes":{"stem":"\u003Cp\u003EA 66-year-old man with type II diabetes is hospitalised for treatment of recently diagnosed acute myeloid leukaemia. Three years ago he had a myocardial infarction, with insertion of two stents. He is on dual antiplatelet therapy. Chemotherapy is started and five days later he collapses with severe chest pain. He is pale and sweating with a blood pressure of 80/60 mmHg. Myocardial infarction is excluded on the ECG and serum troponin. Twenty minutes later his blood pressure is 78/60 mmHg. A CT pulmonary angiogram is performed. (Image) Treatment with a thrombolytic is considered.\u003C/p\u003E","stemQuestion":"Which one of the following is the strongest indication for thrombolytic therapy?","responseType":"sba","marks":1,"options":["The radiological appearances","The presence of diabetes","The blood pressure","The history of myocardial infarction","The dual antiplatelet therapy"],"correctOptions":[2],"correctResponses":null,"explanation":"\u003Cp\u003EIn any patient with collapse and chest-pain, pulmonary embolism (PE) and myocardial infarction (MI) are key differential diagnoses. This is especially true in thrombogenic states such as current cancer. As MI has been excluded by ECG and troponins; a PE is the most likely diagnosis. This is confirmed by the presence of a region of hypodensity in the right main pulmonary artery on CT contrast angiography. This in itself is not an indication for thrombolysis. Thrombolytic therapy in the setting of confirmed PE, is indicated only in patients who are haemodynamically unstable. This patient is \u003Cstrong\u003Ehypotensive\u003C/strong\u003E and in the absence of any other obvious causes, it must be assumed that the haemodynamic instability is consequent on the pulmonary embolus. He requires urgent thrombolysis.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003EA systolic blood pressure of less than 90 mmHg for at least 15 minutes and provided the patient is without high risk for bleeding is an indication for immediate thrombolytic therapy. Thrombolysis comes with its risks, the most important being major bleeding, which may occur in more than 10% of patients being treated this way.\u003C/p\u003E","optionExplanations":null,"learningPoints":["In the presence of a pulmonary embolus, thrombolytic therapy should only be considered in the haemodynamically unstable patient."],"references":["Duffett L, Castellucci LA, Forgie MA. Pulmonary embolism: update on management and controversies. BMJ 2020;370:m2177"]},"relationships":{"itemRevision":{"data":{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"15002"}},"question":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"628"}},"stemMedia":{"data":[{"type":"media","id":"17504"}]},"explanationMedia":{"data":[]}}},{"type":"media","id":"17504","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/media/17504"},"attributes":{"mimeType":"image/jpeg","url":"https://app.emedici.com/storage/media/e7302617-9172-446e-9acc-19826685bef0.jpg","thumbUrl":"https://app.emedici.com/storage/media/e7302617-9172-446e-9acc-19826685bef0.jpg","isProcessed":true,"width":587,"height":425}},{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"15002","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/itemRevisions/15002"},"attributes":{"createdAt":"2022-09-30T17:57:36+09:30","updatedAt":"2024-10-15T15:26:24+10:30"},"relationships":{"item":{"data":{"type":"items","id":"628"}},"content":{"data":{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"28805"}}},"meta":{"canDelete":false}},{"type":"tags","id":"2","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/tags/2"},"attributes":{"emoji":"\ud83e\udec0","name":"Cardiology","synonyms":[],"description":null,"position":null,"createdAt":null,"updatedAt":"2024-11-21T09:47:21+10:30"},"relationships":{"group":{"data":{"type":"tagGroups","id":"1"}},"heading":{"data":{"type":"tagHeadings","id":"1"}